#!/usr/bin/env -S uv run --script
# /// script
# requires-python = ">=3.11"
# dependencies = [
#   "mitmproxy>=11",
# ]
# ///
"""
sakar — network-intercepting sandbox. Splits the network-interception half of sarun
into a standalone tool.

    sakar                   start the server (foreground; Ctrl-C to stop)
    sakar -- CMD [ARGS...]  run CMD in a network namespace whose only connectivity
                            is via sakar's mitmproxy (server must be running first)
    sakar --inner ...       in-box pid-1 runner (spawned by bwrap; not for direct use)

Network model (identical to sarun's net path):
  The box has loopback only. Three in-box rendezvous services forward connections to
  the server's in-process mitmproxy via the box's ONE muxed unix-socket connection:
    • HTTP proxy on 127.0.0.1:8080 — proxy-AWARE clients set HTTP_PROXY here
    • DNS resolver on 127.0.0.53:53 — synthetic 127/8 IPs for proxy-UNAWARE clients
    • Catch-all TCP on :80/:443 — clients dialing a synthetic IP get intercepted

Filesystem: passthrough (--dev-bind / /). sakar's job is network isolation only.
Policy: deny/allow wildcard files in config_home(); interactive prompt for unknowns.
Flows: written as mitmproxy native .mitm files to state_home().
"""

